8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 516, L.D. 1287, “An Act to Support
9 Workforce Development by Establishing the Housing Stability Fund”
10 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 3-D in §4768 in subsection 2 in the last line (page
11 1, line 22 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "distributions received from the fund" and
12 inserting the following: 'an allocation received from the fund and keep the total cost of
13 program delivery and administrative costs to 25% or less of an allocation received from the
14 fund'
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 3-D in §4768 by inserting after subsection 2 the
16 following:
17 '3. Program delivery and operations. The program must include funding and
18 capacity for adequate staffing to support program delivery and operations, facilitate
19 wraparound and navigation services and provide essential stability and case management
20 critical to the success of program participants. An entity delegated to administer the
21 program must be capable of serving a diverse population, including persons with limited
22 proficiency in the English language and from a wide range of cultural backgrounds, and
23 must possess demonstrated experience administering similar programs, including
24 supplemental rental assistance and housing navigation programs. Staff members must
25 substantially participate in ensuring equitable access and program compliance and in
26 connecting renters with broader supports that promote long-term housing stability and
27 workforce participation.'
28 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 3-D in §4768 by renumbering the subsections to
29 read consecutively.
30 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
31 'Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §4641-B, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 559, Pt. I, §4 and
32 affected by §15, is amended to read:
